# To install rustup:
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh
# OR
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs > install-rustup.sh
chmod +x install-rustup.sh
sudo ./install-rustup.sh
rustup component add rust-analyzer

# to update Rust:
rustup update

The Rust book in PDF:
 * https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/print.html and browser "print" or "save as PDF"
 * https://github.com/max-heller/mdbook-pandoc?tab=readme-ov-file#rendered-books
The Rust book built from source (but it doesn't produce PDF, so don't bother):
# Version number at https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/src/tools/rustbook/Cargo.toml
cargo install mdbook --locked --version 0.4.51
cd ~/tmp
git clone git@github.com:rust-lang/book.git rust-lang-book
cd rust-lang-book
cargo install --locked --path packages/mdbook-trpl
mdbook build

===========================================================================

# Install rustfmt:
rustup component add rustfmt
# Run rustfmt:
cargo fmt

===========================================================================

# Install clippy:
rustup component add rustfmt
# Run clippy:
cargo clippy
